headline: Silver prices just hit a 13-year high. More gains could be on the way.
summary: Silver rallied Thursday to tap its highest price in more than 13 years, with the industrial metal finally making a significant move to catch up to gold’s gains, pulling the gold-silver ratio down to its lowest level since the Trump administration’s “liberation day” tariff announcement.

headline: Winnebago says job cuts are coming. Why Trump’s tariffs can be blamed.
summary: Winnebago’s stock dropped after the RV maker issued a profit warning and said it was cutting jobs, as the Trump presidency hasn’t provided the retail momentum that was hoped for.

headline: Dollar Tree has more than just wealthier customers to handle tariffs, analysts say
summary: Truist analysts say they believe Dollar Tree and other retailers have done a better job staying flexible on where they get products.

headline: Apple's woes deepen following Epic Games ruling. Here's where we stand on the stock now
summary: A U.S. appeals court rejected Apple's request Wednesday to halt changes to its App Store, precipitated by its yearslong legal battle with the Fornite maker.

headline: Did Nvidia just dispel the bear case for its stock? Why this analyst thinks so.
summary: The shift from AI training to inferencing, especially for reasoning models, is an opportunity to drive greater GPU demand, the company recently said. Bears have worried about this transition.

headline: Tesla has lost nearly $140 billion in market cap since Elon Musk left DOGE. Here’s what may be ahead for the stock.
summary: Tesla’s stock was on the verge of a technical breakthrough. Then Musk and President Donald Trump had a very public fallout.

headline: Two major retirement changes are on the table for federal workers — whether they’re new or tenured
summary: The House-passed reconciliation bill could impact retirement benefits and worker protections.

headline: Surging electricity demand is just one reason natural gas looks so appealing to investors this summer and beyond
summary: It’s that time of year again, when the need for cooling in the summer heat lifts demand for natural gas — but that’s not the only factor raising the risk for tighter supplies of the fuel.

headline: Did trade wars stop businesses from hiring? The May jobs report will give us the answer.
summary: If the labor market really does begin to suffer ill effects from the trade war, a rising unemployment rate would make it quite clear.

headline: Trump ties his souring relationship with Elon Musk to EVs. Here are the facts.
summary: President Donald Trump and billionaire Tesla CEO Elon Musk continued to clash Thursday, with Trump linking their fraying relationship to his administration’s efforts to reduce support for electric vehicles.
